textDisplay:
Starbucks = sugar with coffee flavour. And as every coffee lover will agree upon, espresso is a bad, automated imitation of the Turkish coffee. Sorry Italian friends no offence :)

Also one important point which took my attention is the claim of the presentator to drink water after drinking an espresso. If this is really the custom in Italy then they really don't know how to drink coffee as if someone drinks water after finishing his coffee then it would mean that the coffee was bad. By drinking water after coffee you want to wash off the bad taste and this would mean an offence in Turkey for the coffee maker. So never, ever drink water after your coffee in a public café or when visiting if you don't want to offend the owner :)

The correct way of drinking coffee is to take a first sip from water to wash your tongue off any other taste and to prepare it for the sensational taste of your coffee. The sips also have a name in Turkey as the first sip is called the acquaintance, the second sip alliance and the third sip addiction if you are enjoying a truly good Turkish coffee.

Last but not least, never drink your coffee alone. At the end “A cup of Turkish coffee will be remembered for forty years.”
